                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d561">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00 Revolutions/44: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-28T17:00:00-06:00"
                            >April 28, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 29—11:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>79. Department’s telegram No. 30, April 27, 7 p.m. Instructions regarding Naval
                    Attachè strictly complied with and views concerning <pb facs="0687" n="567"
                        xml:id="pg_567"/> company’s planes respected. President now considering
                    purchasing an unused plane here belonging to United Fruit Company and manning it
                    with Honduran forces for observation purposes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
